Wind drives @@yyellow@@N grit in low ribbons while @@bbrown@@N retaining walls keep the lane coherent despite branching footpaths.@@N
From this square, a flat @@yyellow@@N glare runs from ridge to ridge, and every marker suggests traders once moved in disciplined columns.@@N
A snapped survey rod is wrapped in three faded cloth bands: blue, yellow, and brown.@@N
~
0 10
D0
A narrow ramp climbs toward another survey-marked square.
~
~
0 -1 8785
D1
The caravan line continues through a bright seam of blown sand.
~
~
0 -1 8806
D2
Footprints descend where the route steps into the next grid lane.
~
~
0 -1 8825
D3
The marked lane curves back toward earlier watch-cairns.
~
~
0 -1 8804
E
route line~
Painted arrows and knot-marks imply the intended progression: west-to-east across a row, then south to the next line.~
